
Overview of noun shiva

The noun shiva has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                        
1. shiva, shivah, shibah -- ((Judaism) a period of seven days of mourning after the death of close relative; "the family is sitting shiva")
2. Siva, Shiva -- (the destroyer; one of the three major divinities in the later Hindu pantheon)
